onsidering whether we need to assert if System.exit isn't reached. Normally, in a JVM, it terminates the process, but I don’t think that applies here. Maybe I could use JUnit's System Lambda, which doesn’t require extra dependencies and works with the SecurityManager. I should remove security manager options. To retain the input handler test, I could try setting the SecurityManager and catch the UnsupportedOperationException. While rules say not to skip native tests, I could verify that startAnt isn’t executed gracefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating startAnt process**\\n\\nI’m noticing that the startAnt process prints “Buildfile: ...” after calling processArgs and before running the build. It looks like it uses System.out for that. After processArgs, it jumps to runBuild. I want to see if we can throw an uncaught Error after addInputHandler but before System.exit. StartAnt catches Throwable around runBuild, prints the stack trace, and then handles the log file before exiting. So it looks like exit is still happening.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2MWURd3vxp7Ql3E3Yue6RfGv|fc_05006304cb6521f80169fbba4f213c81a2a32f2f5c6f9e5fe8", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/MainTest.java", "limit": 320}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 38893, "output": 2630, "cacheRead": 6656, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48179, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778104870628, "responseId": "resp_05006304cb6521f80169fbba27e5a081a29d17500496312f9f"}}
