i9c6kNGZMAVVSZxLraXGgfa9KCT6gY_YRgVsBBNb-tB0bfE9UAyWvmKEj4gz8_4V-1y40ulonju7mdkfou6xRWQYlhg8u_ASDtH_PZi52ohu4WCtQLaVsQhIELotTSb7sUShAPFD6MA63T-yRHP2iM9UllkEeCVe5nttvTANkrgt77NHGNmhi-GsD98RTKwi1Tsmvwc2Ga-RWp0R7E9sYJoA6axwIPedfwzZWI7DuEtnv6eCqunwLV1QN09sByTQEdekZQ04shdRk0OA2f9tRnzdoJCuRLYa_TjgNla2QIFXsQmhCNNHjB2wv7uSzi1JGgYOnuivJLheTKD2fisscFFpIVyuW4BLobONZJXpzulXt4oKtmXzFi99muWl0mf_YXpZ2LtLaCGuB7qyWJiqSAHvLl2Dwt4Za3XLwRJEiD1-fZ_pxeamkOG3cT6X7qZoWNGLc-fYc6RSXOanLVqjI3fdv88Gfsm4ay0rMmQLB-e7Sh-PQ3WYEkGS3w5T_Etv4k8-R-yLC8TKLi-s1PD68-o7lfBGzI6LV6sSrAPw_F2tly6sNQe0jARiyeESRDsgyFKJbV2l3ChYJJNVlm1D6USrFxMkvYJr-FSJ3zSZ1jN1YFikPA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing build issues**\\n\\nI need to fix an issue because JDK 25 doesn't support the security manager, and I can't use the 'SecurityManager'. Also, I need to ensure I don't use 'System.exit' as it causes problems with tests. I'm exploring alternatives for handling input, such as possibly using a public API, but that has complications as well. Subclassing Main or figuring out using 'org.apache.tools.ant.launch.Launcher' might help, but still, I need to avoid situations leading to 'System.exit' calls. Testing in a forked process could be a solution.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring testing options**\\n\\nI'm considering whether dynamic access for harness instruments tests at runtime in the same process. Running a child JVM likely isn't tracked by the agent, which is a concern. I need coverage for dynamic access in the test JVM. Another option might be using MethodHandles, but direct reflection isn't allowed. And if I remove the VM option, will the SecurityManager test throw an UnsupportedOperationException? JDK 25 doesn't support setting the SecurityManager. It's tricky to handle input without calling System.exit. Shadowing System might be impossible, so I’ll have to explore other pathways.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Rethinking error handling**\\n\\nI’m considering whether we need to assert if System.exit isn't reached. Normally, in a JVM, it terminates the process, but I don’t think that applies here. Maybe I could use JUnit's System Lambda, which doesn’t require extra dependencies and works with the SecurityManager. I should remove security manager options. To retain the input handler test, I could try setting the SecurityManager and catch the UnsupportedOperationException. While rules say not to skip native tests, I could verify that startAnt isn’t executed gracefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating startAnt process**\\n\\nI’m noticing that the startAnt process prints “Buildfile: ...” after calling processArgs and before running the build. It looks like it uses System.out for that. After processArgs, it jumps to runBuild. I want to see if we can throw an uncaught Error after addInputHandler but before System.exit. StartAnt catches Throwable around runBuild, prints the stack trace, and then handles the log file before exiting. So it looks like exit is still happening.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2MWURd3vxp7Ql3E3Yue6RfGv|fc_05006304cb6521f80169fbba4f213c81a2a32f2f5c6f9e5fe8", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/MainTest.java", "limit": 320}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 38893, "output": 2630, "cacheRead": 6656, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48179, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778104870628, "responseId": "resp_05006304cb6521f80169fbba27e5a081a29d17500496312f9f"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_2MWURd3vxp7Ql3E3Yue6RfGv|fc_05006304cb6521f80169fbba4f213c81a2a32f2f5c6f9e5fe8", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage ant.ant;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.PrintStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.BuildEvent;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.BuildException;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.BuildListener;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.BuildLogger;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.Main;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.Project;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.input.InputHandler;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.input.InputRequest;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.catchThrowableOfType;\n\npublic class MainTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void addBuildListenersLoadsConfiguredLoggerAndListenerClassesByName() throws IOException {\n        Path buildFile = createBuildFile();\n        CustomBuildLogger.reset();\n        CustomBuildListener.reset();\n\n        ConfiguredMain main = new ConfiguredMain(\n            \"-buildfile\", buildFile.toString(),\n            \"-logger\", CustomBuildLogger.class.getName(),\n            \"-listener\", CustomBuildListener.class.getName(),\n            \"-emacs\",\n            \"-quiet\");\n        Project project = new Project();\n\n        main.addListenersTo(project);\n\n        assertThat(CustomBuildLogger.instances).hasValue(1);\n        assertThat(CustomBuildLogger.messageOutputLevel).isEqualTo(Project.MSG_WARN);\n        assertThat(CustomBuildLogger.output).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(CustomBuildLogger.error).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(CustomBuildLogger.emacsMode).isTrue();\n        assertThat(CustomBuildListener.instances).hasValue(1);\n        assertThat(CustomBuildListener.project).isSameAs(project);\n        assertThat(project.getBuildListeners())\n            .hasAtLeastOneElementOfType(CustomBuildLogger.class)\n            .hasAtLeastOneElementOfType(CustomBuildListener.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void startAntLoadsConfiguredInputHandlerClassByNameBeforeRunningBuild() throws IOException {\n        Path buildFile = createBuildFile();\n        CustomInputHandler.reset();\n        SecurityManager previousSecurityManager = System.getSecurityManager();\n        ExitInterceptingSecurityManager exitSecurityManager = new ExitInterceptingSecurityManager();\n        System.setSecurityManager(exitSecurityManager);\n        try {\n            Main main = new Main();\n\n            ExitInterceptedException exit = catchThrowableOfType(\n                () -> main.startAnt(new String[] {\n                    \"-buildfile\", buildFile.toString(),\n                    \"-inputhandler\", CustomInputHandler.class.getName()\n                }, null, null),\n                ExitInterceptedException.class);\n\n            assertThat(exit).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(exit.status).isZero();\n            assertThat(CustomInputHandler.instances).hasValue(1);\n            assertThat(CustomInputHandler.project).isNotNull();\n        } finally {\n            System.setSecurityManager(previousSecurityManager);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void getAntVersionLoadsVersionResourceThroughMainClassLiteralCompatibilityPath() {\n        String antVersion = Main.getAntVersion();\n\n        assertThat(antVersion).startsWith(\"Apache Ant version \");\n        assertThat(antVersion).contains(\" compiled on \");\n    }\n\n    private static Path createBuildFile() throws IOException {\n        Path directory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"ant-main\");\n        Path buildFile = directory.resolve(\"build.xml\");\n        Files.writeString(buildFile, \"\"\"\n            <project name=\"main-test\" default=\"ok\">\n                <target name=\"ok\"/>\n            </project>\n            \"\"\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        buildFile.toFile().deleteOnExit();\n        directory.toFile().deleteOnExit();\n        return buildFile;\n    }\n\n    private static final class ConfiguredMain extends Main {\n        ConfiguredMain(String... args) throws BuildException {\n            super(args);\n        }\n\n        void addListenersTo(Project project) {\n            addBuildListeners(project);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class CustomBuildLogger implements BuildLogger {\n        private static final AtomicInteger instances = new AtomicInteger();\n        private static int messageOutputLevel;\n        private static PrintStream output;\n        private static PrintStream error;\n        private static boolean emacsMode;\n\n        public CustomBuildLogger() {\n            instances.incrementAndGet();\n        }\n\n        static void reset() {\n            instances.set(0);\n            messageOutputLevel = -1;\n            output = null;\n            error = null;\n            emacsMode = false;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setMessageOutputLevel(int level) {\n            messageOutputLevel = level;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setOutputPrintStream(PrintStream output) {\n            CustomBuildLogger.output = output;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setEmacsMode(boolean emacsMode) {\n            CustomBuildLogger.emacsMode = emacsMode;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setErrorPrintStream(PrintStream error) {\n            CustomBuildLogger.error = error;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void buildStarted(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void buildFinished(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void targetStarted(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void targetFinished(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void taskStarted(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void taskFinished(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void messageLogged(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class CustomBuildListener implements BuildListener {\n        private static final AtomicInteger instances = new AtomicInteger();\n        private static Project project;\n\n        public CustomBuildListener() {\n            instances.incrementAndGet();\n        }\n\n        static void reset() {\n            instances.set(0);\n            project = null;\n        }\n\n        public void setProject(Project project) {\n            CustomBuildListener.project = project;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void buildStarted(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void buildFinished(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void targetStarted(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void targetFinished(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void taskStarted(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void taskFinished(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void messageLogged(BuildEvent event) {\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class CustomInputHandler implements InputHandler {\n        private static final AtomicInteger instances = new AtomicInteger();\n        private static Project project;\n\n        public CustomInputHandler() {\n            instances.incrementAndGet();\n        }\n\n        static void reset() {\n            instances.set(0);\n            project = null;\n        }\n\n        public void setProject(Project project) {\n            CustomInputHandler.project = project;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void handleInput(InputRequest request) throws BuildException {\n            request.setInput(\"\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ExitInterceptingSecurityManager extends SecurityManager {\n        @Override\n        public void checkPermission(Permission permission) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void checkPermission(Permission permission, Object context) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void checkExit(int status) {\n            throw new ExitInterceptedException(status);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ExitInterceptedException extends SecurityException {\n        private final int status;\n\n        ExitInterceptedException(int status) {\n            this.status = status;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778104911577}]}
